{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015ZWxv7EEenk12TgvKZL3Qz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear: \n1. `es-transport` headless service has no endpoints! That's why DNS resolution is failing.\n2. Nodes can't form a cluster because they can't find each other.\n\nThe reason there are no endpoints is that the service's selector doesn't match any pods that are ready. A headless service (ClusterIP: None) adds pods to endpoints based on the pod selector, but with `publishNotReadyAddresses: false` (default), it only adds Ready pods.\n\nSince the pods are not Ready (readiness probe failing), they're not added to the endpoints, which means DNS doesn't resolve, which means nodes can't find each other, which means they can never become Ready - a chicken-and-egg problem!\nThe solution is to enable `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the `es-transport` service so that pods can discover each other during startup, before they pass their readiness checks. I'll update the service definition with this flag.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1528,"cache_read_input_tokens":42598,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1528},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1dbbafb2-5c68-4053-909c-600bf0cd1e93","uuid":"32725eb0-4e1a-46be-82a4-1020b0e0442c","request_id":"req_011CbzKdDLi2hyUJJRFVVL5f"}
