{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DS5UyakaCLQ3pYRNfPhzAM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node Elasticsearch cluster is fully deployed and operational:\n\n**Resources created:**\n- `ConfigMap/elasticsearch-config` — `elasticsearch.yml` with TLS, security, and discovery settings\n- `Service/es-transport` (headless) — inter-node discovery on port 9300 (`publishNotReadyAddresses: true` so nodes can find each other before any are Ready)\n- `Service/es-http` (ClusterIP) — HTTPS client access on port 9200\n- `PodDisruptionBudget/elasticsearch-pdb` — keeps ≥2 nodes up during disruptions\n- `StatefulSet/elasticsearch` (3/3 Ready) — `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all 3 nodes start concurrently and can bootstrap together\n\n**Verification results:**\n- Cluster health: `\"status\":\"green\"`, `\"number_of_nodes\":3`\n- Write: `\"result\":\"created\"`, `\"_shards\":{\"successful\":2}`\n- Read: 2 documents returned correctly\n\n**Key decisions:**\n- `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the transport service solves the bootstrap chicken-and-egg (pods can't become Ready until they form a cluster, but DNS for the headless service only resolves when pods are Ready)\n- `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` ensures all 3 nodes start at once so the initial master election can proceed\n- Transport SSL uses `verification_mode: certificate` (validates CA signature only, not hostname) since the pre-existing cert may not cover per-pod DNS names"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":378,"cache_read_input_tokens":51013,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":378},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1dbbafb2-5c68-4053-909c-600bf0cd1e93","uuid":"48365fe6-7b2b-4c94-9fd0-d545afbc2